    "Rule 1.1 and its comments make clear that a lawyer may take on an unfamiliar matter if she can become competent through necessary study and preparation, or by associating with a lawyer of established competence in the field. Newness to an area is not a bar; inadequate preparation is. The competence duty cannot be waived by the client, because it protects the integrity of representation, not merely the client's preferences.",
