    "Rule 1.4 requires a lawyer to keep the client reasonably informed, promptly comply with reasonable requests for information, and explain matters to the extent reasonably necessary for the client to make informed decisions, especially about settlement. Communication failures are among the most common bases for discipline, entirely apart from the quality of the legal work. Doing good work while leaving the client in the dark is still an ethics violation.",
