    "Rule 1.8(h)(2) allows a lawyer to settle a malpractice claim with an unrepresented or former client only after advising that person in writing of the desirability of seeking independent legal counsel and giving a reasonable opportunity to obtain it. This differs from 1.8(h)(1), which requires actual independent representation before a lawyer may prospectively limit liability. The safeguard exists because the lawyer's interest in settling is directly adverse to the client's.",
