    "Model Rule 4.4(b) provides that a lawyer who receives a document or electronically stored information and knows or reasonably should know it was inadvertently sent must promptly notify the sender. The Model Rule's only affirmative command is notice; it does not, by itself, require the recipient to return or destroy the material, although some jurisdictions and the law of privilege impose additional obligations. The first step is always prompt notice to the sender.",
