    'Transactions with Non-Clients',
    'When silence becomes assisting fraud',
    "A lawyer is closing a deal for a seller-client. The lawyer learns the client has just slipped a materially false financial statement to the buyer to induce the purchase, and the lawyer's continued work would help the fraud succeed. Under Rule 4.1(b), what is the lawyer's obligation?",
